{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|はか}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=はか|-}}. Found in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'', completed some time around 759 CE.

Ultimate derivation {{unk|ja|nocap=1|sort=はか}}. One possibility is that the final ''ka'' may be {{m|ja|処|tr=ka|pos=suffix denoting place}}, as in the term {{m|ja|住み処|tr=sumika||dwelling, home, abode|lit=living place}}.

{{der-top}}
* {{ja-r|墓%穴|はか%あな}}: an [[open]] [[grave]], the [[hole]] where someone is [[buried]]
* {{ja-r|墓%場|はか%ば}}: a [[graveyard]], a [[cemetery]]
* {{ja-r|墓%掘り|はか%ほり}}: a [[gravedigger]]
* {{ja-r|墓%屋|はか%や}}: a [[graveyard]] or [[cemetery]] [[caretaker]]
